Q:13: Create a 3D text, apply appropriate font, style, color. Use : Hover in the
style selector so that the 3D effects appear only when you hover over
the text
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
	<meta charset="UTF-8">
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
	<style>
    	.threeD-text {
        	font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
        	font-size: 2em;
        	font-weight: bold;
        	color: #3498db;
        	position: relative;
        	display: inline-block;
        	transition: transform 0.3s;
    	}

    	.threeD-text:hover {
        	transform: perspective(500px) rotateX(20deg);
    	}
	</style>
	<title>3D Text</title>
</head>
<body>

	<div class="threeD-text">Hover me for 3D effect!</div>

</body>
</html>
